definition.value: A member of the class of biphenyls that consists of a biphenyl ring system substituted by a tetrazole ring at an unspecified position.
An agent and endogenous substances that antagonize or inhibit the development of new blood vessels.
A 3-hydroxyaspartic acid that has S configuration at the carbon bearing the amino group.
A local anesthetic that is used to numb the surface of a body part.
An aspartic acid derivative that is the N-formimidoyl derivative of  L-aspartic acid.
A N-formyl amino acid that is the N-formyl-derivative of L-aspartic acid.

A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is pentanoic acid (valeric acid) substituted with a keto group at C-2 and a methyl group at C-4. A metabolite that has been found to accumulate in maple syrup urine disease.
A carboximidic acid that is  formic acid in which the carbonyl oxygen is replaced by an imino group.
An alanine derivative that is alanine substituted by a 2,6-dichlorobenzoyl group at the N and a 2-(2,6-dichlorophenyl)-6-quinolyl group at position 3.
A 5-deoxyribose phosphate consisting of 5-deoxy-alpha-D-ribose having the phospho group located at the 1-position.
An N-acyl amino acid that is N-(2,6-dichlorobenzoyl)alanine in which one of the hydrogens at the beta position has been replaced by a  N 6-(2,6-dimethoxyphenyl)-2-naphthyl group.
